  "Broker Comment" : "OTHER RELATED ITEM 29C: U4 DISCLOSES WEBER HAS BEEN NAMED AS A DEFENDANT IN A CIVIL COMPLAINT FILED BY THE CALIFORNIA ATTORNEY GENERAL OF JULY 30, 1982 ON BEHALF OF THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA. HE WAS SERVED ON OCTOBER 12, 1982. THE COMPLAINT INVOLVES WEBER'S SALE OF (CALAM) COAL LEASE INTERESTS TO A SINGLE INVESTOR IN 1977 IN THE AMOUNT OF $11,250. THE COMPLAINT ENJOINS ALL DEFENDANTS FROM DISTRIBUTING THE SECURITIES OF CALAM. *** ADDITIONAL INFORMATION REC'D 11/18/85 DISCLOSES CASE NUMBER C-322823, COMPLAINT FOR INJUNCTION AND DISGORGEMENT WAS DISMISSED WITH PREJUDICE ON MARCH 20, 1985. ** (ADDED 7/18/86): ON DECEMBER 4, 1984, THE COMMISSIONER OF CALIFORNIA DEPARTMENT OF CORPORATIONS AND NORMAN C. WEBER , ENTERED INTO A SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT. WEBER AGREED TO PAY INTO A COURT-APPROVED TRUST FUND THE AMOUNT OF $1,500.00 WHICH REPRESENTS APPROXIMATELY 67% OF THE CONSIDERATION PAID TO/OR EARNED BY HIM IN CONNECTION WITH HIS ACTIVITIES ON BEHALF OF THE 1977 CAL-AM PROGRAM. (7/18/86, COPY OF COMPLAINT RECEIVED)   I WAS NAMED AS A DEFENDANT IN A CIVIL COMPLAINT FILED BY THE CALIFORNIA ATTORNEY GENERAL ON JULY 30, 1982 REGARDING THE SALE OF COAL SUB-LEASE INTERESTS WITH WYOMING AND WESTERN COAL RESERVES INC. (STATE OF CALIFORNIE VS. PERMCO, ETC. NORMAN C. WEBER).  THE COMPLAINT REGARDED FURTHER DISTRIBUTION OF THE \"SECURITY\" WHICH HAD NOT BEEN DISTRIBUTED FOR THREE YEARS COMMISSIONS WERE PAID BACK INT A COURT- APPROVED TRUST FUND.  I WS THEN DISMISSED FROM THE CIVIL SUIT WITH PREJUDICE ON 3/26/85."
